'''''88 Poems''''' is a book of the collected poetry of author [[Ernest Hemingway]], published in 1979. It includes a number of poems published in magazines, the poems which appeared in Hemingway's first book, ''[[Three Stories and Ten Poems]]'', and 47 previously unpublished poems that were found in private collections and in the Hemingway papers held by the [[John F. Kennedy Library|Kennedy Library]].<ref name="cover note">{{cite book |last=Hemingway|first=Ernest |authorlink=Ernest Hemingway |author2=Nicholas Gerogiannis |title=88 Poems|year=1979 |publisher= Harcourt Brace Jovanovich, Inc|location= New York|isbn=0-15-128052-5|pages= }}</ref>

